OL,3,CFormer Bristol Rugby captain dies aged
OL,4,C49
OL,6,FFormer Bristol Rugby captain Matt
OL,7,FSalter has died at the age of 49.
OL,9,FSalter captained Bristol for four
OL,10,Fseasons and led the Guinness
OL,11,FPremiership Dream Team in 2006, he
OL,12,Falso played professionally for London
OL,13,FBroncos and Leeds.
OL,15,FFollowing his retirement he dedicated
OL,16,Fhimself to coaching, serving as a Head
OL,17,FCoach at Clifton RFC and Director of
OL,18,FRugby at Clifton College for many
OL,19,Fyears.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/3
