OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1773056483
OL,3,CFormer Bristol Rugby captain dies aged
OL,4,C49
OL,6,FClifton Rugby Club have paid tribute
OL,7,Fsaying: "Matt's impact on the game in
OL,8,FBristol will be felt for many years to
OL,9,Fcome.
OL,11,F"As a player, captain and coach, he
OL,12,Finspired countless teammates, players
OL,13,Fand students, and his passion for
OL,14,Frugby and for helping others develop
OL,15,Fthrough the game was clear to all who
OL,16,Fworked with him.
OL,18,F"Matt will be greatly missed across
OL,19,Fthe Clifton and wider Bristol rugby
OL,20,Fcommunity."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/3
